OL,3,CRetail spending slows as Budget looms
OL,4,Clarge
OL,6,FRetail sales growth slowed in
OL,7,FSeptember as rising inflation and a
OL,8,Fpotentially taxing Budget weighed on
OL,9,Fhouseholds ahead of Christmas, figures
OL,10,Fsuggest.
OL,12,FTotal UK retail sales increased by
OL,13,F2.3% year on year in September,
OL,14,Fagainst growth of 2% in September 2024
OL,15,Fand above the 12-month average growth
OL,16,Fof 2.1%, according to British Retail
OL,17,FConsortium (BRC) and KPMG data.
OL,19,FFood sales were up 4.3% year on year,
OL,20,Fdriven largely by inflation rather
OL,21,Fthan volume growth.
