OL,3,CRetail spending slows as Budget looms
OL,4,Clarge
OL,6,FLinda Ellett, UK head of consumer
OL,7,Fretail and leisure markets at KPMG,
OL,8,Fsaid: "Overall sales grew in
OL,9,FSeptember, driven largely by household
OL,10,Fgoods and increased mobile phone
OL,11,Fsales, as prominent brands launched
OL,12,Fnew models.
OL,14,F"However, non-food sales are only
OL,15,Fgrowing by around 1.2% on average,
OL,16,Findicating that spending continues to
OL,17,Fbe very targeted as consumers remain
OL,18,Fcautious.
